Attribute soccerTeamStatsComplexType / @line-formation
Namespace No namespace
Annotations
 
String representing the formation of the team on the field
starting from the back of the field. This can be written as 4-4-2 where the
hyphens separates the lines on the field from the defense at left to the
forwards to the right. Depending on the formation of the team other than
three digits can be used, for example 4-2-3-1.
Type xs:string
Properties
use: optional
Used by
Complex Type soccerTeamStatsComplexType
Source

  <xs:annotation>
    <xs:documentation>String representing the formation of the team on the field starting from the back of the field. This can be written as 4-4-2 where the hyphens separates the lines on the field from the defense at left to the forwards to the right. Depending on the formation of the team other than three digits can be used, for example 4-2-3-1.</xs:documentation>
  </xs:annotation>
</xs:attribute>
